g_item_descs[9966]="^ffcb4aIt is said that the Kitchen God was once a constellation of Heaven. For some fault he \rcommitted, he was demoted to governing kitchens in man's world. Usually the God of Kitchen\rwould sit in the middle of a kitchen watching how people live, recording both  good and\rbad behavior. On the 23th day of the second month of the lunar calendar, the God of Kitchen will\rreturn to Heaven to make his report. Then, he goes back to his duty on the night of the 30th day of the second month of the lunar\rcalendar. The good and bad are then either rewards or punished. So on every 23th day of the second month of the \rlunar calendar people will offer Tangkua, which is a sweet and sticky snack, to the God of Kichen,\rbelieving that by doing so the God of Kitchen will be unable to report ill-doings because his lips will be stuck together due the yummy candy.";
